A canonical object representing an (external) ontology.
Most attributes are not considered in creating a canonical representation, only the full name.
TODO: Consider adding a field for the ontology format to distinguish OWL, PowerLoom, SNOMED, etc.
TODO: Decide if we want to pull the non-canonical fields out into separate view objects so that there can be multiple ones.
@author University of Southern California @date $Date: 2011-07-20 14:36:26 -0700 (Wed, 20 Jul 2011) $ @version $Revision: 2626 $

A short name for the ontology. If none is set, then the full name will be returned. Not part of the canonical criteria.
@return The short name if one exists, else full name

Changes the short name for the canonical term.
@param name The new short name

The display name is a name designed for GUI display or other computer-human interactions. If none is set, then the short name will be returned. Not part of the canonical criteria.
@return The display name if it exists, else full name.

Changes the display name for the canonical term
@param name The new display name

Changes the description for the canonical term
@param desc The new description

UML_Profile_for_Java:JavaElement.JavaAnnotations: @NamedQueries({@NamedQuery(name="ontology.findAll",query="SELECT x FROM Ontology x"),@NamedQuery(name="ontology.findCanonical",query="SELECT x FROM Ontology x WHERE fullName = :fullName")})
